SIMPLE: godhead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Godhead
<hw>God"head</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>godhed</ets>. See <er>-head</er>, and cf. <er>Godhood</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Godship; deity; divinity; divine nature or essence;
godhood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The Deity; God; the Supreme Being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The imperial throne⟦br⟧
Of <qex>Godhead</qex>, fixed for ever.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A god or goddess; a divinity.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Adoring first the genius of the place,⟦br⟧
The nymphs and native <qex>godheads</qex> yet unknown.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Godhood</ent>⟦br⟧
